<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Manchester City defender Nicolas Otamendi is attracting interest from Porto and Inter Milan. </p>

<p>The 32-year-old could yet be pushed into negotiations with Sevilla for Jules Kounde though the Spanish would prefer a straight cash deal of around £65million for the 21-year-old. </p>

<p>Otamendi has fell down the pecking order at City following Nathan Ake's summer arrival from Bournemouth.</p>

<p>Manchester City defender Nicolas Otamendi is being chased by Inter Milan and Porto</p>

<p>Pep Guardiola is ready to sell Otamendi with the 32-year-old not in his starting XI plans</p>

<p>The Argentinian was not selected in City's match-day squad for their season-opener with Wolves as with Pep Guardiola preferring to partner Ake and John Stones.</p>

<p>Otamendi has made 210 appearances for the club over his five-year spell.</p>

<p>During his at City, he has won two Premier League titles, one FA Cup and four league cups. </p>

<p>City, meanwhile, are keen on adding Estudiantes winger Darío Sarmiento this summer.</p>

<p>The 17-year-old winger has represented Argentina at U16s and U17s level and has been tipped for a bright future. </p>

<p>City may try to use Otamendi in negotiations for Sevilla's £65m-rated star Jules Kounde</p>
